---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | Seetayya Foundation" description="Privacy policy for Seetayya Foundation website visitors.">
  <section class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="container-pad max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-black text-ink">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <div class="rich-content mt-8 text-lg leading-8 text-ink/74">
        <p>At seetayyafoundation, accessible from https://seetayyafoundation.org/, one of our main priorities is the privacy of our visitors. This Privacy Policy explains the types of information collected and recorded by seetayyafoundation and how it is used.</p>
        <p>If you have additional questions or require more information about this Privacy Policy, please contact the foundation.</p>
        <h2>Consent</h2>
        <p>By using this website, you consent to the Privacy Policy and agree to its terms.</p>
        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <p>The personal information that you are asked to provide, and the reasons why you are asked to provide it, will be made clear at the point where the information is requested.</p>
        <p>If you contact the foundation directly, the foundation may receive information such as your name, email address, phone number, message contents, attachments you may send, and any other information you choose to provide.</p>
        <h2>How we use your information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide, operate, and maintain the website.</li>
          <li>Improve, personalize, and expand the website.</li>
          <li>Understand and analyze how visitors use the website.</li>
          <li>Communicate with visitors for service, updates, and information relating to the foundation.</li>
          <li>Send emails and prevent fraud.</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Log files and cookies</h2>
        <p>The old Privacy Policy states that standard hosting log files may collect internet protocol addresses, browser type, internet service provider, date and time stamp, referring or exit pages, and click activity. These are used for trends, administration, movement on the website, and demographic information.</p>
        <p>Visitors can choose to disable cookies through browser options.</p>
        <h2>Children's information</h2>
        <p>The foundation does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under the age of 13 through the website. If you believe a child provided this kind of information, please contact the foundation so it can be removed where possible.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
